    <h3>Community Information</h3>
    <p>Boulder, Colorado is located at the base of the foothills of the Rocky Mountains and is 30 minutes northwest of the state's capital, Denver. Boulder is the most populated city in Boulder County and is home of the main campus of the University of Colorado, the state's largest university. Since the area is considered the high-desert, with an altitude of 5,400 above sea level, the climate is mostly mild with high and low temperatures but very little humidity. Boulder is known as one of the best cities for outdoor activities, so it is filled with people who embrace an active outdoor lifestyle. One of its treasures is The Pearl Street Mall.  Located in downtown Boulder, the mall is a four block long outdoor stretch of endless shopping combined with art galleries and sidewalk cafes. Downtown is also full of seasonal art shows, crafts fairs and free outdoor concerts. Its no wonder the beautifully well-rounded city is frequently top ranked in health, quality of life, education, and art. </p>
